<subSubSection id="C35F6546FFD407770BBB35A49DF08756" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BFA36CDFFD407770BBB35A49F9A82B2" blockId="2.[136,1452,878,1553]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis id="B931EADFFFD407770BBB35A49FB68296" bold="true" box="[189,498,950,976]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
—Forests, grassy slopes; 
<quantity id="4CBD9B28FFD40777081B35A49DF88297" box="[797,956,950,977]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" unit="m" value="2800.0" valueMax="3600.0" valueMin="2000.0">2000–3600 m</quantity>
(based on annotated specimens). 
<collectingRegion id="4981F82FFFD407770E4C35A49BE38296" box="[1354,1447,950,976]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4981F82FFFD407770B8E35C99EA582B3" box="[136,225,987,1013]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4981F82FFFD407770BEA35C89F2F82B2" box="[236,363,986,1012]" country="China" name="Chongqing" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Chongqing</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4981F82FFFD407770A7035C89F9E82B2" box="[374,474,986,1012]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFA36CDFFD407770BBB35EC9DF08756" blockId="2.[136,1452,878,1553]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4EFFD407770BBB35EC9FEE855E" authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; B. N. Wang" authorityYear="1986" box="[189,426,1022,1048]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinfushanense">
<emphasis id="B931EADFFFD407770BBB35EC9FEE855E" box="[189,426,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Lilium jinfushanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described and typified from cultivated material at Kunming Botanical Garden (Peng 84-23!) derived from bulbs originally collected on Jinfo Mountain (
<collectingRegion id="4981F82FFFD40777089032309AF4857A" box="[918,1200,1058,1084]" isEnumeration="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Chongqing and Guizhou</collectingRegion>
provinces). Based on the published material, 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4EFFD407770A9632559C0C8526" authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; B. N. Wang" authorityYear="1986" box="[400,584,1094,1120]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinfushanense">
<emphasis id="B931EADFFFD407770A9632559C0C8526" box="[400,584,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. jinfushanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4EFFD4077709D832559A0C8526" authority="Franchet (1892: 319)" authorityName="Franchet" authorityPageNumber="319" authorityYear="1892" box="[734,1096,1094,1120]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="taliense">
<emphasis id="B931EADFFFD4077709D832559D178526" box="[734,851,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. taliense</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD44B3CFFD40777085C32549A0C8526" author="Franchet, A. R." box="[858,1096,1094,1120]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" pagination="305 - 321" refId="ref6994" refString="Franchet, A. R. (1892) Les Lis de la Chine et du Thibet. Journal de Botanique (Morot) 6: 305 - 321." type="journal article" year="1892">Franchet (1892: 319)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by having more purple spots at the throat of flower and yellowish tepals. However, we have observed purple spots and yellowish flowers in natural populations of 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4EFFD407770A34329D9FE385EE" box="[306,423,1166,1192]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="taliense">
<emphasis id="B931EADFFFD407770A34329D9FE385EE" box="[306,423,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. taliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which occurs in northwestern 
<collectingRegion id="4981F82FFFD40777080F329D9D1B85EF" box="[777,863,1167,1193]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation id="137E2A48FFD407770869329C9DAE85EF" box="[879,1002,1166,1193]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,187,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[154,1434,187,1884]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Flowers of Lilium taliense Franchet from NW Yunnan showng continuous morphological variations in tepal spots andcolor i.e., white to yellow). Materials representing populations from A, Wengshui, Yunnan (Kham Expedition 10-56, PE) showing variability of spot tepal spots; B, Gezan, Yunnan (Kham Expedition 10-10, PE) showing variability of tepal color on a single individual; C, Jinfo Mountain, the type locality of L. jinfushanense exhibiting yellow inner tepals." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5142425" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5142425/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Fig. 2A, B</figureCitation>
). Thus, the spots and tepal color appear insufficient to justify the species status of 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4EFFD40777097F32A19D70858A" authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; B. N. Wang" authorityYear="1986" box="[633,820,1202,1228]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinfushanense">
<emphasis id="B931EADFFFD40777097F32A19D70858A" box="[633,820,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. jinfushanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We more rigorously compared 
<emphasis id="B931EADFFFD407770FA932A19E9B85B6" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4EFFD407770FA932A19B2E858A" authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; B. N. Wang" authorityYear="1986" box="[1199,1386,1202,1228]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinfushanense">L. jinfushanense</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4EFFD407770E9332A19E9B85B6" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="taliense">L. taliense</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
by visiting the 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4EFFD407770A9532C59C0885B6" authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; B. N. Wang" authorityYear="1986" box="[403,588,1238,1264]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinfushanense">
<emphasis id="B931EADFFFD407770A9532C59C0885B6" box="[403,588,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. jinfushanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus id="54FE886FFFD40777095232C59CC085B7" box="[596,644,1239,1265]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">type</typeStatus>
locality at Jinfo Mountain. There, we observed three populations of 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4EFFD407770E9332C59E9B8452" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="taliense">
<emphasis id="B931EADFFFD407770E9332C59E9B8452" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. taliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with inner tepals having yellowish coloring on their adaxial surfaces (
<figureCitation id="137E2A48FFD407770F1232E89A288452" box="[1044,1132,1274,1300]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,187,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[154,1434,187,1884]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Flowers of Lilium taliense Franchet from NW Yunnan showng continuous morphological variations in tepal spots andcolor i.e., white to yellow). Materials representing populations from A, Wengshui, Yunnan (Kham Expedition 10-56, PE) showing variability of spot tepal spots; B, Gezan, Yunnan (Kham Expedition 10-10, PE) showing variability of tepal color on a single individual; C, Jinfo Mountain, the type locality of L. jinfushanense exhibiting yellow inner tepals." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5142425" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5142425/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
) and, thus, bearing striking resemblance to 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4EFFD407770A35330D9FAD847E" authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; B. N. Wang" authorityYear="1986" box="[307,489,1310,1336]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinfushanense">
<emphasis id="B931EADFFFD407770A35330D9FAD847E" box="[307,489,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. jinfushanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We also noticed that the cultivated 
<typeStatus id="54FE886FFFD407770869330D9DDB847F" box="[879,927,1311,1337]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4EFFD407770F29330D9AA0847E" authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; B. N. Wang" authorityYear="1986" box="[1071,1252,1310,1336]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinfushanense">
<emphasis id="B931EADFFFD407770F29330D9AA0847E" box="[1071,1252,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. jinfushanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
exhibits narrower leaves compared to the native populations. We speculate that the observed variation in leaf size may be indicative of unpredictable phenotypic expression under cultivation. The available morphological data appear insufficient for considering 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4EFFD407770A1033999F9784E2" authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; B. N. Wang" authorityYear="1986" box="[278,467,1418,1444]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinfushanense">
<emphasis id="B931EADFFFD407770A1033999F9784E2" box="[278,467,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. jinfushanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a distinct species. Moreover, molecular phylogenetic analyses have resolved the yellow-tepal taxon from the 
<typeStatus id="54FE886FFFD407770ACD33BD9FBF848F" box="[459,507,1455,1481]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">type</typeStatus>
locality within 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4EFFD4077709A833BD9D60848E" box="[686,804,1454,1480]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="taliense">
<emphasis id="B931EADFFFD4077709A833BD9D60848E" box="[686,804,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. taliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD44B3CFFD40777083533BC9DA3848E" author="Gao, Y. D. &amp; Hohenegger, M. &amp; Harris, A. &amp; Zhou, S. D. &amp; He, X. J. &amp; Wan, J." box="[819,999,1454,1481]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" pagination="69 - 85" refId="ref7024" refString="Gao, Y. D., Hohenegger, M., Harris, A., Zhou, S. D., He, X. J. &amp; Wan, J. (2012) A new species in the genus Nomocharis Franchet (Liliaceae): evidence that brings the genus Nomocharis into Lilium. Plant Systematics and Evolution 298: 69 - 85. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00606 - 011 - 0524 - 1" type="journal article" year="2012">
Gao 
<emphasis id="B931EADFFFD40777086D33BD9DDA848E" box="[875,926,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">et al</emphasis>
. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD44B3CFFD4077708F533BC9A78848E" author="Gao, Y. D. &amp; Harris, A. &amp; Zhou, S. D. &amp; He, X. J." box="[1011,1084,1454,1480]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" pagination="443 - 460" refId="ref7112" refString="Gao, Y. D., Harris, A., Zhou, S. D. &amp; He, X. J. (2013 a) Evolutionary events in Lilium (including Nomocharis, Liliaceae) are temporally correlated with orogenies of the Q - T plateau and the HDM. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 68: 443 - 460. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2013.04.026" type="journal article" year="2013">2013a</bibRefCitation>
), and this supports our proposed treatment. A more broadly circumscribed 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4EFFD40777096F33C19CA584AA" box="[617,737,1490,1516]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="taliense">
<emphasis id="B931EADFFFD40777096F33C19CA584AA" box="[617,737,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. taliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D4EFFD40777086033C19A6484AA" authorityName="L. J. Peng &amp; B. N. Wang" authorityYear="1986" box="[870,1056,1490,1516]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinfushanense">
<emphasis id="B931EADFFFD40777086033C19A6484AA" box="[870,1056,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. jinfushanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has yellow and white inner tepal morphs and a wider geographic range in 
<collectingRegion id="4981F82FFFD40777095733E59D568756" box="[593,786,1526,1553]" isEnumeration="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Yunnan, Sichuan</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="4981F82FFFD40777084A33E49DF48756" box="[844,944,1526,1552]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
